CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 20, 1946, pg. 17, reads: "Love in Bloom - Mr. and Mrs. Willis Frazier pledged their troth in a colorful wedding at Central Baptist Church last Saturday evening. The bride is the former Miss Rita Ings, daughter of Mrs. Elsie Ings of Duff Street, and the groom was recently discharged from the Navy. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Groom Willis Frazier wearing tuxedo, and bride Rita Ings Frazier wearing lace trimmed gown, heart shaped headpiece, necklace of three strands of pearls, and holding bouquet, posed in front of window with lace curtains, possibly Ings home on Duff Street
